Tyskl, Schweiz o. Ital. 14, Frankr. 22, Engl. 24 o. 29, Frankr. 33, färdled. v. sv.-tyska skolungd :utb. 27-31. E. o. lär. i AHngsås 22-29, v. Gbgs h. real 29-30, i Linköp. 30-36, adj. i eng. o. franska v. Kalmar h. a. 1 sed. 36.
translated: Jakobsson, Axel Bernhard, high school teacher, Kalmar, b. 15/3/92 in Förlösa, Kalmar 1., son of Karl J. and Emma Petersson. — Graduated from high school in Kalmar in 1913, obtained a Bachelor of Arts from Lund University in 1923, underwent vocational training in Germany, Switzerland, and Italy in 1914, and in France in 1922, went to England in 1924 and 1929, and to France in 1933, led a Swedish-German school youth education program 1927-1931. Was a substitute teacher in AHngsås 1922-1929, at Gothenburg's high school for science 1929-1930, at Linköping 1930-1936, and an adjunct in English and French at Kalmar high school since 1936.
